          "teaching": "Non-invasive positive pressure ventilation (CPAP or BiPAP) reduces work of breathing, offloads the failing LV by decreasing preload and afterload, and improves oxygenation in pulmonary edema. Start early in respiratory distress — it significantly reduces intubation rates and ICU mortality.",
