          "teaching": "Acyclovir 10 mg/kg IV q8h should be added empirically when HSV encephalitis cannot be excluded — it is safe to administer while awaiting CSF HSV PCR results, which take 24–48 hours. HSV encephalitis carries >70% mortality untreated but responds dramatically to early acyclovir. The risk of withholding treatment far outweighs the minimal toxicity risk of empiric dosing.",
