    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Status epilepticus = seizure >5 minutes or recurrent seizures without return to baseline — this is a medical emergency",
      "Treatment ladder: (1) Benzodiazepine → (2) IV fosphenytoin or levetiracetam or valproate → (3) Intubation + propofol/midazolam drip",
      "Medication non-compliance is the #1 cause of status epilepticus in known epileptics",
      "Check glucose IMMEDIATELY — hypoglycemia is the most treatable mimic",
      "Rhabdomyolysis is a major complication — aggressive IV fluids, monitor CK and creatinine",
      "Fever in status epilepticus is from prolonged muscle activity, not necessarily infection — but still consider meningitis/encephalitis"
    ],
