          "aiPatientUpdate": "The ringing in my ears is getting quieter. I can think more clearly. I didn't even know aspirin could do this — I've been taking extra for my arthritis pain for months.",
          "teaching": "✅ Urinary alkalinization working — level decreasing. Key: do NOT intubate (removes compensatory hyperventilation), keep urine alkaline, replete K, add dextrose. If level rises or patient deteriorates → hemodialysis."
