      "Not checking bilateral arm blood pressures — >20mmHg difference is a red flag",
      "Giving tPA for suspected stroke when the cause is actually aortic dissection with carotid malperfusion",
      "Starting anti-impulse therapy with only a vasodilator (causes reflex tachycardia → increased shear stress) — ALWAYS beta-blocker FIRST",
      "Missing cocaine use — key risk factor for dissection in younger patients",
      "Not recognizing that Type B with malperfusion may need urgent intervention (TEVAR) despite 'medical management first' teaching"
