      "Being reassured by a 'normal' exam — neutropenic patients have blunted inflammatory responses",
      "Not covering Pseudomonas — anti-pseudomonal beta-lactam is mandatory empiric coverage",
      "Performing rectal exam or placing rectal thermometer — risk of mucosal breach and bacteremia",
      "Checking ANC only once — must trend to know if patient is at nadir or recovering",
      "Withholding G-CSF because 'oncology hasn't ordered it' — discuss with oncologist but don't delay antibiotics"
