          "critical": false,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Warming an ischemic limb is contraindicated — it dramatically increases the metabolic oxygen demand of the tissue without restoring blood supply, accelerating ischemic necrosis. The ischemic limb should be kept at room temperature or slightly cooled to reduce metabolic demand until perfusion is restored.",
