      "Using vasopressors that worsen limb ischemia (norepinephrine) — optimize cardiac output instead",
      "Not preparing for reperfusion syndrome — hyperkalemia, acidosis, and myoglobin washout can be lethal",
      "Assuming chronic PAD — sudden onset with no prior claudication in a patient with AFib = embolic until proven otherwise"
