      "Osborn (J) waves on ECG are pathognomonic for hypothermia — they resolve with rewarming",
      "If pulseless: CPR + defibrillation (one attempt if <86°F; may withhold further shocks until >86°F as cold myocardium is resistant). Rewarm to >86°F before repeated defibrillation.",
