    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Beck's Triad of tamponade: hypotension + muffled heart sounds + JVD — present in only ~30% of cases but pathognomonic when complete",
      "POCUS is the DIAGNOSTIC TOOL — RA diastolic collapse is the earliest and most sensitive echo sign of tamponade physiology",
      "Pulsus paradoxus >10mmHg = tamponade. Measure: inflate cuff to obliterate all Korotkoff sounds, slowly deflate — first sound heard only in expiration, continue deflating until sounds heard throughout cycle. Difference >10mmHg = positive.",
      "PERICARDIOCENTESIS is the treatment — subxiphoid approach under echo guidance. Removing even 50mL can dramatically improve hemodynamics.",
      "Malignant effusions: lung cancer is the #1 cause. Pericardiocentesis provides diagnosis (cytology) and treatment. Recurrence is common — may need pericardial window.",
      "Tamponade is an OBSTRUCTIVE SHOCK — do NOT give diuretics (reduces preload further) or intubate if possible (positive pressure reduces preload)"
    ],
