      "AIRWAY MANAGEMENT is critical — awake fiberoptic intubation preferred. DO NOT paralyze or sedate (loss of airway tone). Failed intubation → surgical cricothyrotomy. Tracheostomy is technically difficult due to massive neck swelling.",
