          "teaching": "Daily monitoring of platelets, LDH, and peripheral blood smear (schistocyte count) tracks treatment response. Rising platelet count and falling LDH indicate effective thrombosis control. Persistent thrombocytopenia or rising LDH after 2–3 days of TPE signals refractory disease requiring escalation (caplacizumab, rituximab, increased TPE frequency).",
