      "Transfusion reaction (acute hemolytic reaction can trigger DIC — check for fever, hemoglobinuria, but this patient's DIC is from trauma/surgery)",
      "Hypocalcemia from citrate toxicity (ionized calcium 0.82 — replace aggressively)",
      "Abdominal compartment syndrome (check bladder pressure if abdomen distends — massive transfusion + surgical abdomen)"
