      "Not replacing fibrinogen — FFP does not contain enough fibrinogen to correct DIC-level depletion. Need cryoprecipitate or fibrinogen concentrate.",
      "Not rewarming aggressively — hypothermia impairs every step of the coagulation cascade. Warm the blood products and the patient.",
      "Confusing DIC with TTP and withholding platelet transfusion — in DIC, platelet transfusion IS indicated (unlike TTP). DIC + active bleeding = give platelets.",
      "Not rechecking labs frequently — in massive hemorrhage, repeat CBC, coags, fibrinogen, calcium, and ABG every 30-60 minutes to guide transfusion"
