          "teaching": "Serial serum sodium every 2 hours during active correction is mandatory to prevent osmotic demyelination syndrome (ODS). The correction limit is 10–12 mEq/L in 24 hours (some guidelines allow up to 8 mEq/L/24h for the highest-risk patients). If sodium rises too rapidly, DDAVP 2–4 mcg IV can be given to re-lower it by inducing free water retention, combined with D5W infusion.",
