          "teaching": "Red Man Syndrome: direct (non-immune) histamine release from mast cells. Rate-dependent. NOT an allergy. Management: (1) Stop/slow infusion (2) Antihistamine (3) Resume at slower rate (>2h) (4) Premedicate for future doses (5) Document as INTOLERANCE not allergy. True vancomycin allergy (IgE-mediated) is extremely rare and presents with anaphylaxis features."
