          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "HAE type I (85% of cases) has both low C1-INH antigen level and low functional activity. HAE type II (15%) has normal or elevated C1-INH antigen but critically low functional activity — the protein is present but dysfunctional. This distinction matters for diagnosis: always check both C1-INH level AND C1-INH functional assay; level alone will miss type II.",
