          "teaching": "Professional medical interpreter services are legally required and clinically essential when language barriers exist in emergency situations. Family members — especially children — must never be used as interpreters for medical decisions. Inaccurate interpretation of allergy history, trigger identification, and auto-injector education has directly caused preventable anaphylaxis deaths.",
