          "group": "First-line",
          "critical": false,
          "correct": false,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "The standard adult epinephrine auto-injector (EpiPen, 0.3 mg) is the WRONG dose for children under 30 kg. Weight-based dosing is 0.01 mg/kg IM; children under 30 kg should use the 0.15 mg junior auto-injector. Administering the adult dose to a small child risks severe hypertension, reflex bradycardia, and ventricular arrhythmia.",
